history.content:
Computer Science Mentors lead their students in small-group sections and individualized teaching settings, work with a family of like-minded mentors to improve their own teaching, and gain support from the larger community of students, teachers, and mentors in CSM.

 

Apply here to be a part of CSM Fall 2019: http://bit.ly/CSMFa19-Apply.

 

We’re a group of passionate students and mentors who are creating an open and inclusive community for computer science and electrical engineering students to receive individualized academic and social support, and we need your help to make that happen. We are currently recruiting mentors for CS 61A, CS 88, CS 61B, CS 61C, CS 70, EE 16A and EE 16B.

 

Applications are due 11:59 pm, August 18, 2019. More information is in the application, and no late applications will be accepted.

 

For more information, please visit csmentors.berkeley.edu or get in touch with us at mentors@berkeley.edu.
